Ellipsometry, solid-phase spectra of matrices, are given in Fig. 3(f-j) with black lines. For practical use of the optical absorption data, extinction coefficients of the matrices (km
                           ) are determined at the wavelength of the used UV-MALDI MS laser, 355 nm (km355
                           ), which relate how much of the energy of the beam is absorbed in a material (Table 5 inserted in Fig. 5
                           ). The values of km355
                            have the following order CHCA > DHB > AT > F20TPP > 9AA. Based on the km355
                            values, most of the matrix compounds are already well-suited to used 355 nm nitrogen UV-MALDI MS laser (Fig. 3(f-j)). The km355
                            values of all matrices ranged between 2 and 3 (Table 5, Fig. 5), except for the 9AA matrix, which was about 20 times lower.
